description: Perhaps no other car in American automotive history has captured the hearts of consumers more than the Ford Mustang. Since its introduction, its smaller size and its sporty styling made it an instant success among the American public. 50 years later the love affair with the Ford Mustang lives on and has expanded to all 4 corners of the globe.

We are pleased to offer this very cool, purpose built 1968 Ford Mustang Coupe for your consideration. This Mustang is powered by a fortified 289 V8 fed by a 4 barrel carburetor, the powered is transferred via a 3-speed automatic transmission and delivered by a Ford 9' rear end. The car has been fully restored and professionally prepared, highlights include Mustang II style front suspension,  according to the owner new dual Flowmaster exhaust, new fuel tank, all new rear springs and shackles, new shocks, all new stainless steel brake and fuel line, balanced drive shaft, the owner added a new Pertronix ignition, and Edelbrock air cleaner, X-pipe, etc. The interior is outstanding and highly trimmed with newer seats, carpet, dash, suede headliner, and modern analog style gauges with carbon fiber accents, and wood steering wheel, also added was a center console, a modern AM/FM radio and CD player, and the always recognizable sequential lights. The motor has fresh mechanicals and the engine bay is extremely cleaned, detailed and features smoothed firewall, and deleted shock towers. The fit, finish, and presentation of this ‘68 mustang is stunning, with an outstanding Presidential Blue metallic paint with classic white stripes, rear integrated spoiler, hood scoop, fog lights, rear valance exhaust, and American Racing Torque Thrust Wheels. Complementing the stunning presentation of this tastefully modified Mustang is the performance. It is a complete blast to drive, vintage power combined with modern steering and suspension adds confidence to the driver. You cannot build it to this level at the price offered here.

description: This very tastefully modified Mustang is one of those cars that everyone can love but few can own. With a few upgrades that will make it stand out from the rest of the Mustangs at the next show, it's a cool cruiser with enough horsepower to give it the performance to back up the look.

Repainted in brilliant Signalflare Red, this Mustang is proof that bright red on an early Mustang is always the right choice. It was originally plain old Wimbledon White, but that's not what you need if you crave attention like this pony does. The paint job is a few years old, applied over good, straight bodywork with crisp panel details that really pop no matter how closely you look. No need for fake Shelby add-ons or other styling gimmicks, the original Mustang coupe is an icon and wears its handsome curves quite well. Fit and finish are good overall and suggest that this Mustang probably started out as a nice car before the work started; you don't get doors that close like that from a beater. There are a few signs of use today and it's not a show-quality paint job, but a trip to the detail shop for a cut and buff would really wake it up. We're also guessing that the trim is a combination of original and replacement pieces, but it all looks right and shines up nicely against the red paint. Perhaps most importantly, it carries '289' emblems on the front fenders, and it earns them the old-fashioned way.

Inside there's a correct red and white Pony interior, which has been restored to factory specs with nicely upholstered buckets that look incredibly inviting. There's no damage, and only minor signs of use, which only adds to its appeal. A modern three-spoke steering wheel frames the original gauges, and with a trio of auxiliary gauges under the dash it's easy to keep an eye on things under the hood. There's an AM/FM/CD stereo in the original radio's location, and it sounds pretty good all things considered. Black carpets keep it from being too bright inside and the shifter is easy to reach from the driver's seat. The little Mustang also offers a surprisingly roomy trunk, as well, one which includes a new mat and a full-sized spare tire assembly.

This was originally an F-code car, which is a 260 cubic inch V8, but it now runs a later 289, which is OK by us. Besides, nobody will be able to tell the difference at a glance. It's a bit grungy under the hood, so nobody's going to suspect anything has changed, and you can see that there are several upgrades like the Edelbrock 4-barrel carburetor, finned valve covers, and a new water pump on the front of the block. It runs great and pulls hard at any speed, and history has taught us that these engines are virtually bulletproof. The C4 3-speed automatic transmission shifts well and spins a set of 3.00 gears, so this pony is a fantastic high-speed touring car that's quite comfortable in today's traffic. description: Just Toys Classic Cars is very proud to present this stunning 1967 Ford Mustang.  This is a numbers matching car that has had one repaint in its original Raven Black and as you can see in the pics it has had some Shelby esk accents on the trunk.  This car is in great shape.  It is something that you would be very proud to drive down the road and show off in.  As you can see, the black paint shines very well.  This is about a 5 year old paint job.  If you are like some of us and just have an obsession for Mustangs, then this is the car you need.    As you look in the interior you will see that the black vinyl seats are in awesome shape.  They were recovered and you don't see any rips or tears in them, the headliner, or the carpet.  The gauges have been upgraded to white face and the oil pressure and temp gauges have been put in to pods on the A pillar.  You will also see that on the lower side of the steering column is a small tach so you can see everything that is going on with your pony.  You will also enjoy all of your favorite tunes with the upgraded AM/FM radion in the stock location.  The upgraded steering wheel looks awesome in this interior as well.  This truly is a car that you must have in your garage.    Under the hood sits the original 289 the car was born with.  The miles that you see on the odometer are what are on the car.  This is mated to the original C4 transmission and all of that goes out through the stock rear end as well.  This car has plenty of great options like power steeing, power front disc brakes, and A/C.
